"a.(药物)镇静的；n.镇静剂 【英】 adj. (药物)镇静的(tendin g to calm excitement);n. 镇静剂(a sedative drug) 【考】 sedative : drowsiness / anesthetic : numbness(镇静剂使人想睡/麻 醉剂使人麻木)sedative : pacify / antiseptic : sterilize(镇静剂可以使人平静 /杀菌剂可以杀菌) adj. (药物)镇静的; n 镇静剂(有安慰、镇定或起安静效果的) 【类】sedative: drowsiness = anesthetic: numbness镇静剂使人想睡 = 痲醉剂使人麻木sedative: pacify = antiseptic: sterilize镇静剂可以使人平静 = 杀菌剂可以杀菌 【记】近于settle 使平静，安定 sedative (adj.)  ""tending to calm or soothe,"" early 15c., from Medieval Latin sedativus ""calming, allaying,"" from sedat-, past participle stem of sedare, causative of sedere ""to sit"" (see sedentary). The noun derivative meaning ""a sedative drug"" is attested from 1785. Hence, ""whatever soothes or allays."""
